# zarlcode .env example. Copy this to a `.env` next to your shell
# (project root, or ~/.config/zarlcode/.env), uncomment what you
# want to override, and run `go run ./zarlcode/cmd` — no inline
# `LLM_BASE_URL=… LLM_MODEL=…` prefix needed.
#
# Process env still wins over file values — `LLM_MODEL=other go run …`
# overrides whatever the file says. Missing files are skipped silently.

# --- LLM provider --------------------------------------------------

# Provider backend. One of: llamacpp, openai. Default: llamacpp.
# LLM_PROVIDER=llamacpp

# Base URL of the OpenAI-compatible endpoint. For llama-server, the
# OpenAI-compatible path is /v1.
LLM_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8081/v1

# Model name the provider sends in the request. For llama-server this
# is mostly informational (the server only has one loaded model anyway).
LLM_MODEL=qwen3.6-35b-a3b

# Reasoning mode (Qwen3 supports a <think>…</think> phase). Default true.
# LLM_THINKING=true

# Hard context window of the loaded model. Match your llama-server -c
# flag so the proactive compactor knows when to fire. Default 49152
# (Qwen3.6-35B-A3B served window).
# LLM_CONTEXT=49152

# Headroom kept below the context window when deciding to compact.
# Default 8192 ≈ one full turn's growth.
# LLM_RESERVE=8192

# --- zarlcode knobs --------------------------------------------

# Max tool-call iterations per turn. Default 50.
# MAX_ITERATIONS=50

# Glamour-rendered markdown for assistant content. Default true.
# MARKDOWN=true

# Glamour theme. Auto, dark, light, notty. Default dark (the auto
# detection mis-fires on non-TTY hosts).
# GLAMOUR_STYLE=dark

# Max concurrent registry-tool calls per LLM tool-call batch. <=1
# disables parallelism (historical behaviour). Default 4.
# ZARLCODE_TOOL_CONCURRENCY=4

# Workspace directory the agent operates in. When unset, zarlcode
# walks up from the cwd looking for a go.mod and uses that module
# root, or falls back to a fresh /tmp dir.
# WORKSPACE=/path/to/your/workspace

# --- Home Assistant MCP (optional) ---------------------------------

# HA_MCP_URL=http://homeassistant.local:8123/mcp
# HA_MCP_TOKEN=eyJ…

# --- Misc ----------------------------------------------------------

# Disable colour output (https://no-color.org/).
# NO_COLOR=1
